Package flowchart

Interface Summary
AbstractStatement An instance of interface AbstractStatement is a statement, for example a primitive statement, an IF statement, a WHILE statement, or a sequence of statements.
 

Class Summary
ChartConfig The configuration for painting a flowchart, including the size, the position and the color of each element in the flowchart.
FlowchartSymbolFactory This is a factory for creating symbols in a flowchart.
IfStatement A IF statement consists of a condition (denoted by a diamond) and one or two branches (represented by a StatementSequence respectively).
LabelDimension A utility class for calculating the height and width of a label in HTML format.
Module An instance of a Module consists of zero or more instances of Procedure, which are held in a Map.
PrimitiveStatement This is an abstraction of a sequence of primitive statements (e.g. assignments and I/O statements).
Procedure An instance of a Procedure consists of a sequence of statements.
StatementSequence An instance of a StatementSequence contains a list of instance(s) of AbstractStatement.
WhileStatement A WHILE statement consists of a condition (denoted by a diamond) and one loop body (represented by a StatementSequence).
